The '''Musée des Abattoirs'''-(which translates to museum of slaughterhouse),is a museum in the [[France|French]] south-west, in the city of [[Toulouse]], capital of the [[Haute-Garonne]] ''[[departments of France|département]]''. The museum opened in 2000 in a former [[slaughterhouse]] from 1823 and houses an important collection of [[Modern art|Modern]] and [[Contemporary art]].

